## Building on a Debian system:

1. `apt-get install` [live-helper](http://packages.qa.debian.org/l/live-helper.html) or rather use the latest from 'deb http://live.debian.net/debian/ ./'
1. `git clone git://git.debian.org/git/debian-live/config-webc.git`
1. webconverger/ is the base config file for [[maxi]]
1. Take a long good look at [scripts/config](http://git.debian.org/?p=debian-live/config-webc.git;a=blob;f=mini/scripts/config)
1. `lh_config` to setup the configuration (this is the new live-helper 'autoconfig' style)
1. `sudo lh_build` in webconverger/ to kick off the long build process

Then [[test|testing]] your freshly built image.

1. [[todo]] has a list of bugs that need to be fixed. Please help Webconverger out and you will be [[acknowledged|acknowledgements]] for your contribution.
1. Check out the [testing setup guide](http://wiki.debian.org/DebianLive/Howto/Creating_a_Test_environment) for testing with netboot on native hardware
1. Join the [Debian Live](http://debian-live.alioth.debian.org/) community. Peruse the [debian-live mailing list archives](http://lists.debian.org/debian-live/). :)

## Debugging mode with the build Webconverger image

Debugging in Webconverger simply involves removing `nosudo` from the [[boot]] options.

